---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import WorkTimeline from "@components/WorkTimeline.astro";
import GithubContributions from "@components/GithubContributions.astro";
import Link from "@components/Link.astro";
import { SITE, SOCIALS } from "@consts";
---

<Layout title="About" description="Learn more about Regina Castro.">
  <Container>
    <aside data-pagefind-ignore>
      <section class="animate space-y-4">
        <h1 class="font-semibold text-3xl" style="color: var(--primary-color);">About me</h1>
        <p>
         I'm <i>Regina</i>, a designer living in Germany.<br>  
         I have more than 6 years of experience working in the UX field, and currently getting my M.Sc. in Human-Computer Interaction at the University of Siegen.
        
        </p>
          <img
              src="src/assets/real-me.jpg"
              alt="Profile picture of Regina Castro"
              class="rounded-16"
            />
          <h2 class="mt-8">What do I do?</h2>
          I design digital interfaces and products, with a strong focus on understanding user needs, motivations, and pain points rather than just building features. 
          My strongest skill is my ability to empathize with users while also understanding business needs and collaborating closely with engineers to design technically feasible solutions. 

          I can write my own front-end code using HTML and CSS and can understand and use AI tools to generate JavaScript (with throrough testing). with a sharp focus on performance, accessibility, scalability & modular design. 
          <br>
          My pet peeves are: 
          - Non-responsive designs that don't work across different screen sizes and devices
          - Interfaces that don't follow accessibility best practices, especially for screen reader users
          - Over-reliance on static mockups instead of building interactive prototypes to validate ideas early
          - Designs that prioritize visual polish and fancy animation over solving real user problems
          <br>

           </p>
          </p>
          <p>
          My recent experience focuses on human-AI interaction,
          accessibility & developer tools. I feel comfortable working through the whole design process,
          from gathering requirements based on user research, designing using Figma/Penpot, and building components using HTML/CSS and JS with a sharp
          focus on performance, accessibility, scalability & modular design.
          </p>
          <p>For my Master’s thesis, I am currently developing an AI-assisted, open-source web extension specifically for
          blind and low-vision (BLV) developers. This project allowed me to
          combine my passion for open-source software and developer tools with a deep technical
          challenges: building usable, context-based LLM interfaces that are fully accessible for screen reader users.
          </p>
          <h2>My skills</h2>
          <div class="skills-cards flex flex-col gap-6">
            <div class="flex gap-3 not-prose group block overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-black/15 bg-white p-3 transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-black/30 hover:shadow-sm focus-visible:-translate-y-0.5 focus-visible:border-black/30 focus-visible:shadow-sm dark:border-white/20 dark:bg-neutral-900 dark:hover:border-white/40 dark:focus-visible:border-white/40">
              <div><h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Engineering</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2">
                <li>Clean HTML/CSS implementation</li>
                <li>Accessibility compliance and inclusive design, with a focus on screen reader users</li>
                <li>Responsiveness, performance and Core Web Vitals</li>
              </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 not-prose group block overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-black/15 bg-white p-3 transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-black/30 hover:shadow-sm focus-visible:-translate-y-0.5 focus-visible:border-black/30 focus-visible:shadow-sm dark:border-white/20 dark:bg-neutral-900 dark:hover:border-white/40 dark:focus-visible:border-white/40">
              <div><h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Design</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2">
                <li>Systematic thinking</li>
                <li>Careful attention to detail and visual polish as well as solving business and user problems</li>
              </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 not-prose group block overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-black/15 bg-white p-3 transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-black/30 hover:shadow-sm focus-visible:-translate-y-0.5 focus-visible:border-black/30 focus-visible:shadow-sm dark:border-white/20 dark:bg-neutral-900 dark:hover:border-white/40 dark:focus-visible:border-white/40">
              <div><h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Research</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2">
                <li>Replacing assumptions with evidence-based findings from user feedback</li>
                <li>Usability testing and user/stakeholder interviews</li>
              </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h2 class="mt-8">Values and principles</h2>
          <p>I am at my best in collaborative environments that value detail-oriented design and evidence-based decision-making. My work is guided by the following principles:</p>
            <ul>
              <li class="list-disc py-1 ml-4 text-lg">"Ship to Learn" mindset: I prioritize building interactive prototypes over static mockups to uncover technical constraints and user insights early in the lifecycle.</li>
              <li class="list-disc py-1 ml-4 text-lg">Accessibility as a foundation: I advocate for WCAG compliance to ensure products are inclusive by design.</li>
              <li class="list-disc py-1 ml-4 text-lg">Design engineering: I look to collaborate with engineers with "the front of the front-end", to design with technical constraints in mind and translate them into code solutions.</li>
              <li class="list-disc py-1 ml-4 text-lg">AI-Augmented workflows: I embrace using AI-assisted development to quickly validate ideas. This allows me to spend more time refining the details and the "human" side of the interface</li>
            </ul>
      </section>
      <section class="animate space-y-6 mt-12">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-y-2">
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">Work</h2>
        </div>
        <WorkTimeline />
      </section>
      <section class="animate space-y-4 mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">Let's Connect</h2>
        <article>
          <p>
            If you want to get in touch with me about something or just to say
            hi, reach out on social media or send me an email.
          </p>
        </article>
        <ul class="not-prose flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {
            SOCIALS.map((SOCIAL) => (
              <li class="flex gap-x-2 text-nowrap">
                <Link
                  href={SOCIAL.HREF}
                  external
                  aria-label={`${SITE.TITLE} on ${SOCIAL.NAME}`}
                >
                  {SOCIAL.NAME}
                </Link>
                {"/"}
              </li>
            ))
          }
          <li class="line-clamp-1">
            <Link
              href={`mailto:${SITE.EMAIL}`}
              aria-label={`Email ${SITE.TITLE}`}
            >
              {SITE.EMAIL}
            </Link>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <GithubContributions />
    </aside>
  </Container>
</Layout>
